  "body": "## Summary\n- **Configurable task history**: Replace the binary \"show finished tasks\" toggle with a time-window selector (1 week, 1 month, 3 months, or all time) to control how much completed work appears in your lists.\n- **Direct task ID search**: Typing a task ID (e.g., \"#123\") in the search bar now performs an instant server lookup when no local matches exist.\n- **Streamlined approvals**: Approval workflows now display exactly how many approvals are required and hide placeholder entries for deleted users; eligible approvers are grouped and collapsible to reduce clutter.\n- **Smarter notes & attachments**: File attachments from task notes now appear in the dedicated Attachments section, while comment threads display only user-authored discussions (filtering out system-generated attachment records).\n\n## Changes\n\n### Task History & Visibility\n- **Granular finalized task controls**: Choose from Last 7 days, 30 days, 90 days, or All time to determine how much finalized task history loads. Workspace and sidebar counts now always reflect active (non-finalized) tasks only, providing stable navigation metrics regardless of your history view settings.\n- **Status-aware filtering**: Status pill counts dynamically update to reflect the selected time window (e.g., showing \"Completed\" counts for the last 7 days when that filter is active).\n\n### Search & Navigation\n- **Exact ID lookup**: Search terms like \"#123\" or \"123\" now trigger direct server queries to locate specific tasks by ID when they aren't cached locally.\n\n### Approvals & Task Details\n- **Improved \"any-of\" approval UI**: When only a subset of team members needs to approve (e.g., \"1 approval needed from any of 5 people\"), the list of eligible approvers is collapsed by default to reduce visual noise. Expand to see specific team members.\n- **Cleaner approver lists**: Removed placeholder entries for deleted users who have not yet responded; displays only active users and those who have already approved or rejected.\n- **Contextual approval hints**: Added explanatory text clarifying flexible approval rules (e.g., \"Only 1 approval is needed — any eligible approver can approve\").\n\n### Notes, Comments & Attachments\n- **Unified attachment view**: Files attached via task notes now surface in the task's Attachments section with full metadata and download/view actions.\n- **Filtered comment threads**: Comments now exclude system-generated attachment metadata, showing only user-authored discussion threads.\n- **Mobile task notes support**: Full support for creating and viewing task notes on mobile with proper categorization of content types.\n\n## Technical Notes\n- **Build 40** (`d129cd0`)\n- **Storage migration**: Migrated from boolean `SHOW_FINISHED_TASKS_STORAGE_KEY` to `FINALIZED_TASK_WINDOW_DAYS_STORAGE_KEY` supporting values `7`, `30`, `90`, or `'all'`.\n- **Database**: Updated SQLite queries to support `recentFinishedStatuses` and `recentFinishedSince` parameters for efficient time-window filtering of finalized tasks by completion date.\n- **API**: Added optional `source` field to `TaskNoteResponse` to distinguish between `comment` and `task_attachment` origins.\n- **Architecture**: Introduced `isTaskAttachmentNote` and `isVisibleTaskNote` utilities with unit test coverage for consistent note categorization across screens.",
